If you don't- that's fine too! Just copy the step above, look after your hair, let it grow etc.If you really want to color it, do so, although it isn't recommended since it'll be a struggle to maintain healthy looking hair because you have to keep touching up the roots (especially if you have very dark hair)! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a9/Look-Like-Candice-Swanepoel-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Look-Like-Candice-Swanepoel-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a9/Look-Like-Candice-Swanepoel-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Look-Like-Candice-Swanepoel-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
